											<section class="main bio authorbio">
							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/abby-mcbride/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p><p class="p1">Abby McBride is a sketch biologist and science writer based in Down East Maine. She has studied, sketched, and written about wildlife (especially seabirds) from New England to New Zealand, working with institutions such as the Fulbright Program, the National Geographic Society, and the Cornell Lab of Ornithology.</p></p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="520" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/abby-bio-520x520.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/abby-bio-520x520.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/abby-bio-1200x1200.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/abby-bio-150x150.jpg 150w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/abby-bio-768x768.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/abby-bio-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/abby-bio-2048x2048.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/abby-bio-900x900.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
